# IntelliRecon backend environment — copy to `.env` and fill in.
# The backend uses the Anthropic SDK, which reads these automatically.

# ── Option A: local LLM bridge (recommended — see llm-bridge/README.md) ─────
# A local LiteLLM proxy (started automatically by `npm run dev`) exposes an
# Anthropic-compatible endpoint backed by Groq — a genuinely separate free-tier
# quota from OpenRouter's shared one — falling back through more Groq models
# and then OpenRouter. Get a free Groq key at console.groq.com (no card;
# don't confuse it with xAI/Grok at console.x.ai, keys starting "xai-", which
# is a paid API with a one-time trial credit, not a real free tier).
ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8471
ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-litellm-generate-your-own-random-string
ANTHROPIC_MODEL=intellirecon-primary
LITELLM_MASTER_KEY=sk-litellm-generate-your-own-random-string
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your-groq-key
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-your-openrouter-key

# ── Option B: OpenRouter directly (or any Anthropic-compatible gateway) ─────
# Uses Bearer auth against the gateway's /v1/messages endpoint. Comment out
# Option A above and uncomment these instead.
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-or-v1-your-openrouter-key
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=nvidia/nemotron-3-ultra-550b-a55b:free
# Optional, OpenRouter-only: comma-separated model slugs (max 3) to transparently
# retry on when the primary model errors — throttled, down, or moderation-flagged.
# Free OpenRouter models share one account-wide 16-req/min quota, so a free model
# here dodges a single-model/provider outage but NOT a free-tier rate limit —
# put a paid model last as the guaranteed safety net.
# ANTHROPIC_FALLBACK_MODELS=meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free,qwen/qwen3-coder:free,deepseek/deepseek-chat-v3.1

# ── Option C: Anthropic API directly ───────────────────────────────────────
# Leave ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL / ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN unset and use:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# Optional: override the backend port (default 8899)
# PORT=8899

# ── HackerOne Hacker API (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Personal API token from https://hackerone.com/settings/api_token/edit
# (read-only hacker-scoped token, NOT a program/customer API token).
# Powers the "hackerone" MCP server (server/mcp-hackerone.mjs): program
# scope lookup, hacktivity search, and your own report history.
HACKERONE_API_USERNAME=your-hackerone-username
HACKERONE_API_TOKEN=your-api-token
